{"cursor":"1083","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nIn sociology, a 'group action' is a situation in which a large number of agents\ntake action simultaneously in order to achieve a common goal; their actions are\nusually coordinated.\n\nGroup action will often take place when social agents realise they are more\nlikely to achieve their goal when acting together rather than individually.\nGroup action differs from group behaviours, which are uncoordinated, and also\nfrom mass actions, which are more limited in place.\n","linknr":165,"url":"Group_action_(sociology)","recorded":1362477159,"links":20,"instances":["philosophy","sociology"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Group processes","Sociological terminology","Sociology index"],"headings":["See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/SNA_segment.png/180px-SNA_segment.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg/40px-Vista_Login_Manager_Cropped.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["agency","philosophy"],["mass_action","sociology"]],"members":["agency","mass_action"],"related":["Sociology","Agency_(philosophy)","Social_action","Group_behaviour","Mass_action_(sociology)","Social_relation","Social_action","Affectional_action","Interpersonal_relationship","Instrumental_action","Traditional_action","Value-rational_action","Interpersonal_relationships","Collective_effervescence"]}